The paper deals with the problem of sparse recovery from subsampled matrices, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Hadamard matrices is a common technique in compressed sensing (cs.DS) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The paper also discusses the restricted isometry property, which is a concept in signal processing (cs.SI).
